    "title": "My richest treasures in life are the moments I get to spend with family. It’s easy to forget this truth when we’re caught in the constant rush and demands of everyday life. Yet, when we pause, we realize that true wealth is found in these connections. Human life was never meant to run on high alert forever, we are meant to slow down, to breathe, and to cherish the people around us. Here are glimpses from my first four days in Vihiga County, where I went to lay my grandmother to rest. She lived a full 101 years, a testament to grace and resilience. In those days, I shared laughter, stories, and silence with my aunts, cousins, nephews, and nieces. Moments I will carry with me. I am deeply grateful for this life, never entitled, always a gift. 📸 Oppo Find X8  🎨 Adobe Lightroom Mobile  #oppofindx8 #shotonoppo #digitaldiary #shotonoppo #vihiga ",
